Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.56,0:05:01.53,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what you asked for, Asakusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.53,0:05:03.57,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Red bean soup and green soybean mochi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.57,0:05:05.54,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent work, Kanamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.54,0:05:09.91,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,If you're that curious, you could \Nalways head down there yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.91,0:05:11.97,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I don't do well in crowds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:16.33,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Kanamori? Where's my change?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.18,0:05:20.34,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm taking it as a service fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:29.30,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why, Asakusa, did you expect to \Nget my labor without compensation?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:31.31,sign_7896_70_Vollleyball,Tent roof signs; right to left,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz299.6}Volleyball
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:31.31,sign_7896_70_Vollleyball,Tent roof signs; right to left,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(509,214)\frz299.6\c&H5A8ABE&}Tennis
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.30,0:05:31.31,sign_7896_70_Vollleyball,Tent roof signs; right to left,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz303.5\fs14\pos(424,57)\c&HA2AD7D&}Water Polo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:33.31,main,Glasses,0000,0000,0000,,It's the age of robots! The time has come for—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.62,0:05:35.58,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I didn't think it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.02,0:05:39.78,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, Kanamori, my friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.78,0:05:40.96,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.96,0:05:42.29,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I'll buy you some milk,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.29,0:05:44.01,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,so would you come see the screening by the anime—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.01,0:05:45.44,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely not. Sounds lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.44,0:05:46.98,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.98,0:05:49.91,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I'll up it to two bottles of the milk \Nthey sell at the Ongyoku Bathhouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.91,0:05:53.65,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Is this like how some people only go to\N the bathroom as part of a group, Asakusa?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.65,0:05:55.75,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I'd feel weird going alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.43,0:05:58.66,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why the anime club, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.66,0:06:00.93,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, because I love anime, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.93,0:06:03.75,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why not make something at home, on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:07.51,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to make anything more \Nthan a short on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.51,0:06:13.47,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And I need the right kind of environment,\N and an opportunity to get anything done.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.47,0:06:17.62,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,And that means you spend your days \Njust staring out at the campus?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.62,0:06:21.69,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly are you looking at, Your Excellency?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.69,0:06:24.19,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious, Kanamori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.19,0:06:26.99,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this campus, built on the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.50,0:06:26.99,sign_9219_95_Shibahama_High_S,Building sign,0000,0000,0000,,Shibahama High School
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.99,0:06:28.74,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The continued renovations, over time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.74,0:06:30.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,have created a layout both\N complicated and inexplicable!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.49,0:06:32.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,A total lack of consistency \Nbetween upper and lower levels!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.49,0:06:34.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The bridges that go into town!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:36.41,sign_9459_96_Shibahama_High_S,Building sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,280)}Shibahama High School
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.49,0:06:36.71,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That clock, which isn't visible \Nfrom most of the campus!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.75,0:06:39.80,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Which means we usually end up looking at...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:42.02,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The clock over on the coast!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.02,0:06:44.25,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It's a public building shaped like a dungeon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.67,0:06:47.22,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I want to make an anime with \Nthis school as the setting!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.22,0:06:50.63,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It's gonna look like this! What do you think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.61,0:06:56.14,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,You get fired up at the drop \Nof a hat, don't you, Asakusa?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.54,0:06:58.26,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what you want me to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.65,0:07:05.01,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,We just enrolled here, and you've\N got all this... stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.01,0:07:09.54,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have anything better \Nto do with your energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.54,0:07:12.00,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, let's go to the anime \Nclub's screening, Kanamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:15.47,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Make it four bottles of milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.47,0:07:16.87,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You're taking advantage of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:19.18,sign_10475_112_A_V_Room_A,Door signs,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(335,80,335,-20)\frx28\fry14\frz342.4}A/V Room A
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:19.87,sign_10475_113_Anime_Research_G,Door signs,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz348.7\move(195,260,195,125)}Anime Research Group\NSpecial Screening
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.87,0:07:22.55,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Go on, go on. Head in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.05,0:07:25.50,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop using me as a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.38,0:07:28.15,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't seem to be very busy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.15,0:07:30.22,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Let's sit in the back, Kanamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.53,0:07:40.83,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Let's sit somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.83,0:07:43.23,main,Club,0000,0000,0000,,Start it up, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:54.24,sign_3058_45_Conan_of_the_Los,Title sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(229,56)}Conan\N{\fs21\b0}of the Lost Island
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.10,0:07:57.74,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What about this is entertaining to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:08:00.09,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You have this simple-looking, round machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.09,0:08:03.17,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,that can fly thanks to a \Nunexplained anti-gravity device,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.17,0:08:05.71,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,which is depicted with an \Nattention to fine details...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:07.58,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Like how they pick it up with their hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.58,0:08:10.17,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It's like when you push a car, \Nhoping the engine will turn over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:11.96,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,They're taking the obvious \Nvisual cues of the animation
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.96,0:08:13.63,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,and using it to create an air of reality!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.70,0:08:18.47,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The spacing of the frame...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.47,0:08:19.41,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Establishing the location...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.41,0:08:21.46,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The relaxed pace that's set by the running!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.46,0:08:24.48,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The way it sets up the character's physicality!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.02,0:08:26.98,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And this sense of scale!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.98,0:08:31.10,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the size contrast created \Nin this crossover shot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.10,0:08:32.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And by having debris flying around,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:35.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,it creates a real sense of propulsion!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:38.01,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And the movement of the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.01,0:08:40.20,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,With the character running against it,\N showing the resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.20,0:08:41.33,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,and how it pushes them around...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.33,0:08:42.12,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:44.81,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You take something that's totally implausible,\N but pass it off like it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.81,0:08:48.31,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You take reality and then exaggerate \Nit in a way that makes sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.31,0:08:51.76,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,A character moves around on top of \Na background, and it creates an entire world!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:55.33,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing a character wandering around a mysterious \Nworld fills you with a sense of adventure—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.87,0:08:56.17,top,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, and you can stop now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.17,0:08:59.17,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Getting more of an explanation than \Nyou asked for is excruciating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.17,0:09:00.36,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.36,0:09:03.56,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I'll admit, anime is more \Ncomplicated than I ever thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:10.62,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, you in the hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.62,0:09:14.40,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. I'm a first-year, too! \NTsubame Mizusaki! I like anime, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.40,0:09:15.61,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, close! Uh, yes! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.61,0:09:18.01,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to spring this on you,\Nbut I need to borrow your hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.01,0:09:18.62,main,Goons,0000,0000,0000,,There she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.62,0:09:20.40,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, are those MiBs?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.40,0:09:21.82,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, see you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.38,0:09:24.62,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, my hat? Where'd it—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:27.47,italics,Movie?,0000,0000,0000,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.47,0:09:29.03,italics,Movie?,0000,0000,0000,,Kana!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.38,0:09:32.37,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,A young girl, fleeing from villains...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.37,0:09:35.54,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,She's actually a famous fashion model...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.54,0:09:37.54,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,On top of being the daughter \Nof some huge megacorp's boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:39.55,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I thought there were anti-monopoly \Nlaws to get rid of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:42.68,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,This smells like cash...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:44.02,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.71,0:09:55.94,sign_14235_166_Strawberry_Milk,Package sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(440,1)}Strawberry Milk
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:56.97,sign_14289_167_Strawberry_Milk,Package sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(270,0,270,360)\c&H242D65&\3c&H79787C&\frx34\fry358}Strawberry Milk
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.41,0:10:00.33,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.35,0:10:02.55,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.75,0:10:09.35,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,What are they talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.35,0:10:10.62,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I can't hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.07,0:10:18.76,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,If this is just a lecture, you didn't\N need to follow me to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:21.26,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking forward to the \Nanime club's screening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.73,0:10:27.02,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand why I'm supposed to put\N on an act just because my parents both do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.02,0:10:30.52,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I want a normal life! Going home with \Nmy friends, doing after school activities!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.52,0:10:34.27,main,Goon,0000,0000,0000,,Our orders are to keep you \Nfrom joining the anime club.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.23,0:10:37.85,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,So if it was live action or any other \Nkind of film club, it'd be fine?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.85,0:10:38.24,main,Goon,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.74,0:10:43.17,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Asakusa...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.07,0:10:47.25,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Go and make friends with Mizusaki, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:53.04,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Being an animator is a real job!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.04,0:10:54.46,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,You breathe life into all kinds of roles!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.46,0:10:57.64,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,And not just people, but wind, \Nthe environment, machines...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:11:00.34,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes they create performances \Nbigger than anything live action could!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.34,0:11:01.37,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.02,0:11:05.01,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,You're the girl who had the hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.01,0:11:06.93,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sup! Sorry about the delay!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.93,0:11:08.60,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I was late catching my bike! Can you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.60,0:11:09.98,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's almost 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:13.91,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we chill on the roof and chow \Ndown our lunches, Tsubamecchy Mizusaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.82,0:11:17.63,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, there's a weirdo lurking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:18.95,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.95,0:11:21.24,main,Goon,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Who are you, exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.27,0:11:22.88,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Run for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.88,0:11:24.37,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Hey, hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:24.99,main,Goon,0000,0000,0000,,Get back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.51,0:11:26.16,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.82,0:11:32.04,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Go up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.81,0:11:37.67,main,Goon,0000,0000,0000,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:10.25,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,That guy works for my parents!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.25,0:12:13.47,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Thankfully, he's tough enough that\N that probably didn't hurt him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.47,0:12:15.78,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you grabbed me when I was taking a sip,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.78,0:12:17.21,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,and now I'm covered in strawberry milk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:18.91,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I am so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.91,0:12:22.21,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of crazy you thought he \Nwas some kind of bad guy, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.21,0:12:25.53,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Sending someone to spy on you at school...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.53,0:12:27.68,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Your parents keep you on \Na short leash, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.68,0:12:29.89,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, Kanamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:32.22,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,They won't shut up about \Nwanting me to be an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.22,0:12:34.65,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not allowed to join the anime club,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.65,0:12:36.56,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,so I told him to get me a \Nstrawberry milk and slipped away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.82,0:12:40.49,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Not that it matters now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:42.53,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I smell like strawberry milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:44.46,top,Crowd,0000,0000,0000,,That's Mizusaki Tsubame!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:56.46,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,No sense in chatting with an audience.\N Let's get you cleaned up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.99,0:13:02.89,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Kanamori, I'm not sure we should \Nbe butting in this much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.89,0:13:07.18,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What're you saying? First you save \Nthe princess, then comes the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:10.97,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't about rescuing a princess \Nfrom a villain! It's a family disagreement!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.97,0:13:14.91,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I know you heard her talk about anime, Asakusa.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.27,0:13:17.61,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just escort her to the laundromat for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.61,0:13:19.46,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You're scheming something up,\Naren't you, Kanamori?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.47,0:13:24.15,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Is this where you sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:26.62,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusaki, that's where actual people sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.62,0:13:27.91,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, someone lives here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.93,0:13:32.01,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.01,0:13:33.83,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,This is the laundromat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.83,0:13:36.85,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, it doesn't exactly give\N off the impression of cleanliness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:40.07,sign_19585_228_Coin_Laundry,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1842,1)}Coin Laundry
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:40.07,sign_19585_229_Rear_Entrance_On,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(234,56)\frz266.8\frx18\fry0}Rear Entrance\N{\c&H475058&\fad(1842,1)}Ongyoku Bathhouse
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:40.07,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Why is it in such an out-of-the-way place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.07,0:13:43.59,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,There's a walkway on the second floor \Nthat leads to the Ongyoku Bathhouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.59,0:13:45.78,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why's the air conditioner on the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.78,0:13:47.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of places have cramped entrances.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.77,0:13:52.81,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It's bigger on the inside than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:55.53,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,This place is a bit like my secret hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.81,0:13:56.81,sign_19968_235_Detergent,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz7.325\frx26\fry338\pos(249,58)\fad(800,1)}Detergent
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:56.81,sign_19968_235_Detergent,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz7.325\frx26\fry338\pos(161,68)\fad(320,1)}Detergent
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:14:01.82,sign_20064_237_Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,Change Machine
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.73,0:14:00.02,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Take this as an apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.02,0:14:01.82,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, you didn't have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:09.98,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I've got some cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.98,0:14:11.07,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.07,0:14:13.52,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, just think of it as an investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.52,0:14:16.41,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,There's a waiting room on the second floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.55,0:14:34.08,sign_20897_245_Coin_Laundry,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(235,265,235,-25)}Coin Laundry
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.91,0:14:47.69,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I love weird buildings like this. \NCan never draw them right, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.50,0:14:52.07,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You draw, Mizusaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:54.38,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I want to be an animator.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.38,0:14:56.43,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of things do you draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.30,0:15:00.21,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.01,0:15:11.11,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say, Asakusa?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.65,0:15:14.26,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell she's serious \Nabout being an animator.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.26,0:15:16.01,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of figure drawing,\N the kind I have trouble with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.01,0:15:18.13,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,You draw too, Asakusa?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.13,0:15:20.49,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.65,0:15:22.85,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.85,0:15:24.01,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.01,0:15:24.95,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.48,0:15:28.65,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Kanamori, who said you could—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.97,0:15:31.74,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.74,0:15:35.24,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,These are... image boards \Nand concept designs right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.65,0:15:38.47,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,E-E-Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.07,0:15:41.00,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,What's an image board?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.00,0:15:43.90,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It's the art done early in \Nanime production to establish
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.90,0:15:45.96,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,the look and feel of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.71,0:15:49.80,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:52.32,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I've wanted to make anime \Never since elementary school,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.32,0:15:54.25,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,and this is the kind of \Nstuff I would always draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.25,0:15:57.93,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,But you're the first person to ever\N recognize that it was concept art.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.86,0:16:01.88,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I've never met anyone who \Ndid concept design before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.88,0:16:04.56,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Most people just do character art. Including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.39,0:16:09.03,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,This is amazing... It's full of ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.38,0:16:15.74,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,You want to try an overlay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.31,0:16:26.85,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It's like my art has a background!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.85,0:16:28.21,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That worked better than I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.54,0:16:29.98,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.98,0:16:30.86,main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.57,0:16:33.74,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,How about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:34.67,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.67,0:16:35.45,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:36.93,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It looks good! This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.25,0:16:40.30,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,This is starting to get interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.85,0:16:45.27,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusaki, how would you like to make \Nanime with Midori Asakusa here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.14,0:16:48.27,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not allowed to join the anime club.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:50.70,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Where'd that come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.70,0:16:53.24,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I have any experience, \Nor know-how, or the guts to—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:56.18,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Why should a pair of bright young people
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.18,0:16:58.83,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,let nonsense like that stop them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.83,0:17:02.34,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to make anime or not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.34,0:17:03.62,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't join the anime club,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:06.37,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,then you can just start a new club of your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.69,0:17:09.75,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,We've got youth on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.75,0:17:12.23,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,That means we don't stand to lose \Nanything here. There's no risk involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.23,0:17:16.59,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,And I may not know anything about anime,\N but I can back you up in other ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.59,0:17:18.26,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.62,0:17:23.14,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Because a famous fashion model making \Nanime sounds like a great way to rake in cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.14,0:17:24.25,main,Both,0000,0000,0000,,You want money?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.65,0:17:29.47,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,This ship is cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.47,0:17:33.39,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,You think? I just drew it because I \Nfelt like I needed to try and do something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:34.90,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,other than characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.43,0:17:43.29,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Asakusa, try drawing some \Nlines on the frame there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.29,0:17:44.91,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,A couple of safety stripes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.11,0:17:50.87,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and pull mine out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.42,0:17:59.23,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,What do you suppose it does, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.23,0:18:02.03,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't thought about it, \Nbut I guess it's for construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:04.47,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, some arms \Nand winches would be good!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.47,0:18:05.26,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Winches?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:06.84,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Like the kind for spooling cables!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.84,0:18:08.27,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea! Put some on!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.76,0:18:10.03,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Does it look good here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.03,0:18:11.48,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:15.36,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Y'know, I've never done any concept art before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.36,0:18:17.43,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I like setting up concepts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.43,0:18:20.20,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ever draw a layout for a \Nsecret base when you were a kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.51,0:18:22.07,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That was always a ton of fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.33,0:18:27.09,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I remember adding traps\N and setting mines...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.09,0:18:29.25,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Not sure who they were supposed to be for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:33.27,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The greatest world I can imagine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.27,0:18:35.03,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I draw to bring that world to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:39.41,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,so concepts are what it's all about!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.75,0:18:43.43,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something, Asakusa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.74,0:18:47.38,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, let's keep going! \NMaybe it should have a light around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.38,0:18:49.94,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That'd make the engine look kind of cramped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.94,0:18:55.23,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like it better if it moved around \Nin a more distinct way, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.17,0:18:58.45,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,How about something like this? \NWings like you'd see on a bug.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.45,0:18:59.97,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wow! That's awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.17,0:19:03.53,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It can't really land like that, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.98,0:19:05.87,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Let's add some landing gear with \Ntires for a counterweight,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.87,0:19:08.54,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,and turn the ducted fans into \Ncontra-rotating propellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:11.07,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,We can attach a tail to make \Nit look like a dragonfly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.23,0:19:20.24,sign_27602_333_All_Purpose_Mann,Title sign,0000,0000,0000,,All-Purpose {\c&H2A3547&\3c&H9FADC5&}Manned Flying Pod\N{\fs30\c&H5B595F&\3c&HA6C0CE&}Kairi
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.50,0:19:12.29,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.29,0:19:13.14,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.14,0:19:16.79,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,And the wings' surfaces\Nare made of solar panels!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.79,0:19:17.90,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, the structure for
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.90,0:19:20.24,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,the wing joints is modeled after \Nreal exoskeletons and muscle fibers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.95,0:19:21.89,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It's tiny!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.89,0:19:23.60,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be, to be light enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.35,0:19:32.35,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's do a motion \Ncheck for the wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.87,0:19:40.01,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,All good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:46.78,main,Goons,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.66,0:19:49.47,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! Let's get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.55,0:19:52.48,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,The switch for the launch \Ncatapult is on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:53.25,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.61,0:19:57.00,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,There was a door here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.19,0:20:00.11,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.14,0:20:05.62,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.62,0:20:07.33,italics,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It says number three is empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.33,0:20:10.02,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That means there's no steam pressure! \NThe catapult's not gonna work!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:12.44,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I'll push! Kanamori, help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.44,0:20:13.98,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.73,0:20:23.21,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.47,0:20:39.65,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,All right! Get in, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.27,0:20:54.81,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:11.86,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It worked! We're actually flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.23,0:21:15.92,sign_30551_356_Ice,Enemy fighter sign,0000,0000,0000,,Ice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:29.85,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Is there no way out of here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:31.86,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,There are massive skyscrapers \Nin every direction!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.86,0:21:33.35,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.35,0:21:34.35,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.35,0:21:35.15,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It's too narrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.15,0:21:35.85,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,We'll fly sideways!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.85,0:21:37.26,main,Tusbame,0000,0000,0000,,It's not gonna work!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.62,0:21:39.36,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:40.58,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.58,0:21:42.06,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,One of the wings isn't responding!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.65,0:21:44.32,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,It took a hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.32,0:21:46.32,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.32,0:21:48.30,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us can figure this out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:49.90,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Kanamori, let's try and shift the weight!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.90,0:21:51.20,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, for the love of...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.21,0:22:00.25,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.75,0:22:12.15,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.34,0:22:23.15,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,This... It's the greatest world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.53,0:22:39.48,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Is it just me, or did we go somewhere awesome?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.48,0:22:41.94,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,It felt like we saw something amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.55,0:22:44.63,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, shoot, I need to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.63,0:22:46.76,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,The new anime by the animation dream team of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.76,0:22:48.82,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue-san, Ohira-san, and Iso-san is gonna air!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.82,0:22:49.36,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you record it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.36,0:22:50.65,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotta see it live!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.94,0:22:53.99,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Which way is the station?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.99,0:22:55.64,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the shortest route!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.64,0:22:57.93,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,I am not running.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.93,0:22:59.91,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,But you always get better times than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.91,0:23:01.80,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusaki, how fast can you do 100 meters?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.80,0:23:03.95,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,When I was little, I used to say \NI could do it in one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.95,0:23:05.65,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Then we can get to the station in eight seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:09.49,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,Whoever's last to the station \Nhas to treat me to something.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.49,0:23:10.48,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.48,0:23:11.54,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.54,0:23:12.32,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,That's cheating!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.32,0:23:14.69,main,Kanamori,0000,0000,0000,,You two are the ones who \Ndecided to just stand around!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.69,0:23:15.46,main,Midori,0000,0000,0000,,Why wouldn't we?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:17.23,main,Tsubame,0000,0000,0000,,Kanamori, you're too fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.97,0:23:24.45,italics,Laundry,0000,0000,0000,,Your washing is done. Please unload the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.45,0:23:28.35,italics,Laundry,0000,0000,0000,,Your washing is done. Please unload the machine.
